707462f-a.title: Brooklyn: Wyona St. - Fulton St.
707462f-a.text:
Wyona AVe., east side, between Fulton Street and Atlantic Ave., show-
ing the Trinity Church (P.E.).  Lyman Cobb, shortly after settling in East
New York in 1850, orgahized the Episcopal Society, which in 1854 purchased
this edifice from the Congregation of the Reformed Church. This structure
built for church services in 1840, was no longer used as one in 1916. The
real estate maps of 1929 show a 4-story brick building on the site.
About 1880.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

704583f-a.title: Brooklyn: Fulton Street - Wyona Street
704583f-a.text:
2729-2733 Fulton Street, north side, between Wyona and Bradford Streets,
showing a former German Roformed Church. Rev. John Escheinaun was the
minister in 1874. It is not designated as a church in 1929.
1922.
